cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the problem of improving the spectral and energy efficiencies of cellular networks through underlay in-band device-to-device (D2D) multicast communication. The paper focuses on the tradeoff between spectral efficiency (SE) and energy efficiency (EE) in a single cell D2D integrated cellular network, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a power allocation algorithm to solve the EE maximization problem, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also involves multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with the dissemination of the same content via direct links in a group. Finally, the paper deals with security and cryptography (cs.CR) as it involves the sharing of the uplink channel with multiple cellular users.
